</code></pre>
<p>I then tried to write a testing helper, to allow me to specify an input and an
expected output and to have it try and parse the input and assert its equality
with some expeted output.</p>
<p>The problem is, I want to create the <code>State&lt;'e&gt;</code> inside the function, with the
<code>'e</code> lifetime referring to the functions body. My generic attempt at writing this
was:</p>
<pre class="lang-rs prettyprint-override"><code>pub fn test_input_output&lt;'i, ExOut, POut, P&gt;(
    input: &amp;'i str,
