//!
//! Key points:
//! 1. On Cortex-M0+ (thumbv6m), atomic operations like fetch_add are not lock-free
//! 2. critical-section provides mutual exclusion by disabling interrupts
//! 3. Inside a critical section, all memory accesses are effectively atomic
//! 4. We must use Ordering::SeqCst to maintain proper synchronization with code
//!    that might access the atomic from interrupt handlers or other cores

